325 static int32_t MmwDemo_RFParser_parseCtrlConfig
326 (
327  MmwDemo_RFParserOutParams *outParams,
328  uint8_t subFrameIdx,
329  MMWave_OpenCfg *openCfg,
330  MMWave_CtrlCfg *ctrlCfg,
331  float rfFreqScaleFactor
332 )
333 {
334  uint16_t frameChirpStartIdx;
335  uint16_t frameChirpEndIdx;
336  int16_t frameTotalChirps;
337  uint32_t profileLoopIdx, chirpLoopIdx;
338  bool foundValidProfile = false;
339  uint16_t channelTxEn = openCfg->chCfg.txChannelEn;
340  uint8_t channel;
341  uint8_t numRxAntennas;
342  int32_t i;
343  uint16_t numLoops;
344  int32_t retVal = 0;
345  int32_t errCode;
346 
347  /***********************************************
348  * Sanity Check on ADC configuration
349  ***********************************************/
350  /* Only support 16 Bits ADC out bits */
351  if(openCfg->adcOutCfg.fmt.b2AdcBits != 2U)
352  {
353  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOTSUPPORT__NON_16BITS_ADC;
354  goto exit;
355  }
356 
357  /* Only support complex ADC data format */
358  if((openCfg->adcOutCfg.fmt.b2AdcOutFmt != 1U) &&
359  (openCfg->adcOutCfg.fmt.b2AdcOutFmt != 2U))
360  {
361  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOTSUPPORT__NON_COMPLEX_ADC_FORMAT;
362  goto exit;
363  }
364 
365  /***********************************************
366  * Parse openCfg
367  ***********************************************/
368  /* Find number of enabled channels */
369  numRxAntennas = 0U;
370  for (channel = 0U; channel < SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL; channel++)
371  {
372  if(openCfg->chCfg.rxChannelEn & (0x1U << channel))
373  {
374  outParams->rxAntOrder[numRxAntennas] = channel;
375  /* Track the number of receive channels: */
376  numRxAntennas++;
377  }
378  else
379  {
380  outParams->rxAntOrder[channel] = 0U;
381  }
382 
383  //add check to make sure lambda/2
384  //check for rxAnt -= 1, 2, 4 and their limitations
385  }
386  outParams->numRxAntennas = numRxAntennas;
387 
388  /***********************************************
389  * Parse frameCfg
390  ***********************************************/
391  /* Read frameCfg chirp start/stop index */
392  frameChirpStartIdx = MmwDemo_RFParser_getChirpStartIdx(ctrlCfg, subFrameIdx);
393  frameChirpEndIdx = MmwDemo_RFParser_getChirpEndIdx(ctrlCfg, subFrameIdx);
394  numLoops = MmwDemo_RFParser_getNumLoops(ctrlCfg, subFrameIdx);
395  frameTotalChirps = frameChirpEndIdx - frameChirpStartIdx + 1;
396 
397  /* TODO::Advance Frame only support one burst - chain limitation, */
398  if (ctrlCfg->dfeDataOutputMode == MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_ADVANCED_FRAME)
399  {
400  if(ctrlCfg->u.advancedFrameCfg.frameCfg.frameSeq.subFrameCfg[subFrameIdx].numOfBurst != 1)
401  {
402  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOTSUPPORT__NON_ONE_NUMOFBURST_FOR_ADVANCED_FRAME;
403  goto exit;
404  }
405  }
406 
407  /* since validChirpTxEnBits is static array of 32 */
408  if(frameTotalChirps > 32U)
409  {
410  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOIMPL__NUM_UNIQUE_CHIRPS_MORE_THAN_32;
411  }
412 
413  /* loop for profiles and find if it has valid chirps */
414  /* we support only one profile in this processing chain */
415  for (profileLoopIdx = 0;
416  ((profileLoopIdx < MMWAVE_MAX_PROFILE) && (foundValidProfile == false));
417  profileLoopIdx++)
418  {
419  uint32_t mmWaveNumChirps = 0;
420  bool validProfileHasElevation = false;
421  bool validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = false;
422  uint16_t validProfileTxEn = 0;
423  uint16_t validChirpTxEnBits[32]={0};
424  MMWave_ProfileHandle profileHandle;
425 
426  profileHandle = MmwDemo_RFParser_getProfileHandle(ctrlCfg, profileLoopIdx);
427  if (profileHandle == NULL)
428  continue; /* skip this profile */
429 
430  /* get numChirps for this profile; skip error checking */
431  retVal = MMWave_getNumChirps(profileHandle, &mmWaveNumChirps, &errCode);
432  if (retVal != 0)
433  {
434  retVal = errCode;
435  goto exit;
436  }
437 
438  /* loop for chirps and find if it has valid chirps for the frame
439  looping around for all chirps in a profile, in case
440  there are duplicate chirps
441  */
442  for (chirpLoopIdx = 1; chirpLoopIdx <= mmWaveNumChirps; chirpLoopIdx++)
443  {
444  MMWave_ChirpHandle chirpHandle;
445  retVal = MMWave_getChirpHandle(profileHandle, chirpLoopIdx, &chirpHandle, &errCode);
446  if (retVal != 0)
447  {
448  retVal = errCode;
449  goto exit;
450  }
451  /* get handle and read ChirpCfg */
452  {
453  rlChirpCfg_t chirpCfg;
454  retVal = MMWave_getChirpCfg(chirpHandle, &chirpCfg, &errCode);
455  if (retVal != 0)
456  {
457  retVal = errCode;
458  goto exit;
459  }
460  {
461  uint16_t chirpTxEn = chirpCfg.txEnable;
462  /* do chirps fall in range and has valid antenna enabled */
463  if ((chirpCfg.chirpStartIdx >= frameChirpStartIdx) &&
464  (chirpCfg.chirpEndIdx <= frameChirpEndIdx) &&
465  ((chirpTxEn & channelTxEn) > 0))
466  {
467  uint16_t idx = 0;
468  for (idx = (chirpCfg.chirpStartIdx - frameChirpStartIdx);
469  idx <= (chirpCfg.chirpEndIdx - frameChirpStartIdx); idx++)
470  {
471  validChirpTxEnBits[idx] = chirpTxEn;
472  foundValidProfile = true;
473  }
474  }
475  }
476  }
477  }
478  /* now loop through unique chirps and check if we found all of the ones
479  needed for the frame and then determine the azimuth/elevation antenna
480  configuration
481  */
482  if (foundValidProfile) {
483  int16_t nonElevFirstChirpIdx = -1;
484  for (chirpLoopIdx = 0; chirpLoopIdx < frameTotalChirps; chirpLoopIdx++)
485  {
486  bool validChirpHasElevation = false;
487  bool validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = false;
488  uint16_t chirpTxEn = validChirpTxEnBits[chirpLoopIdx];
489  if (chirpTxEn == 0) {
490  /* this profile doesn't have all the needed chirps */
491  foundValidProfile = false;
492  break;
493  }
494 
495  /* check if this is an elevation TX chirp */
496  validChirpHasElevation = (chirpTxEn == MmwDemo_RFParserHwCfg.elevTxAntMask);
497  validProfileHasElevation |= validChirpHasElevation;
498 
499  /* if not, then check the MIMO config */
500  if (!validChirpHasElevation)
501  {
502  uint8_t log2TxEn;
503 
504  /* If only TX antenna is enabled, then its 0x1<< log2TxEn should equal chirpTxEn */
505  log2TxEn = mathUtils_floorLog2(chirpTxEn);
506  validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = (chirpTxEn == (1 << log2TxEn));
507 
508  /* if this is the first chirp without elevation, record the chirp's
509  MIMO config as profile's MIMO config. We dont handle intermix
510  at this point */
511  if (nonElevFirstChirpIdx == -1) {
512  validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp;
513  nonElevFirstChirpIdx = chirpLoopIdx;
514  }
515 
516  /* if this is the first chirp, record the chirp's
517  MIMO config as profile's MIMO config. We dont handle intermix
518  at this point */
519  if (chirpLoopIdx == 0)
520  {
521  validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp;
522  }
523  /* check the chirp's MIMO config against Profile's MIMO config */
524  if (validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp != validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp)
525  {
526  /* this profile doesnt have all chirps with same MIMO config */
527  foundValidProfile = false;
528  break;
529  }
530  }
531 
532  /* save the antennas actually enabled in this profile */
533  validProfileTxEn |= chirpTxEn;
534  }
535  }
536 
537  /* found valid chirps for the frame; mark this profile valid */
538  if (foundValidProfile == true) {
539  rlProfileCfg_t profileCfg;
540  uint32_t numTxAntAzim = 0;
541  uint32_t numTxAntElev = 0;
542  rlProfileCfg_t ptrProfileCfg;
543 
544  outParams->validProfileIdx = profileLoopIdx;
545  /* Get profile id from profile config */
546  retVal = MMWave_getProfileCfg(profileHandle, &ptrProfileCfg, &errCode);
547  if (retVal != 0)
548  {
549  retVal = errCode;
550  goto exit;
551  }
552 
553  outParams->numTxAntennas = 0;
554  if (validProfileHasElevation)
555  {
556  numTxAntElev = 1;
557  }
558  if (!validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp)
559  {
560  /* BPM ?*/
561  numTxAntAzim = 1;
562  }
563  else
564  {
565  uint8_t log2TxEn;
566 
567  while(validProfileTxEn)
568  {
569  log2TxEn = mathUtils_floorLog2(validProfileTxEn);
570  if ((0x1 << log2TxEn) & MmwDemo_RFParserHwCfg.azimTxAntMask)
571  {
572  numTxAntAzim++;
573  }
574  validProfileTxEn &= ~(0x1<< log2TxEn);
575  }
576  }
577 
578 #ifdef MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_DBG
579  System_printf("Azimuth Tx: %d (MIMO:%d), Elev Tx:%d\n",
580  numTxAntAzim,validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp,numTxAntElev);
581 #endif
582 
583  outParams->numTxAntennas = numTxAntAzim + numTxAntElev;
584  if (outParams->numTxAntennas > SYS_COMMON_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS)
585  {
586  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_EINVAL_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS;
587  goto exit;
588  }
589 
590  outParams->numVirtualAntAzim = numTxAntAzim * outParams->numRxAntennas;
591  outParams->numVirtualAntElev = numTxAntElev * outParams->numRxAntennas;
592  outParams->numVirtualAntennas = outParams->numVirtualAntAzim +
593  outParams->numVirtualAntElev;
594 
595  /* Sanity Check: Ensure that the number of antennas is within system limits */
596  if ((outParams->numVirtualAntennas <= 0) ||
597  (outParams->numVirtualAntennas > (SYS_COMMON_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS * SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL)))
598  {
599  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_EINVAL__NUM_VIRTUAL_ANTENNAS;
600  }
601 
602  /* Copy the Rx channel compensation coefficients from common area to data path structure */
603  if (validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp)
604  {
605  for (i = 0; i < outParams->numTxAntennas; i++)
606  {
607  outParams->txAntOrder[i] = mathUtils_floorLog2(validChirpTxEnBits[i]);
608  }
609  }
610 
611  outParams->validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp;
612 
613  /* Get the profile configuration: */
614  retVal = MMWave_getProfileCfg(profileHandle,&profileCfg, &errCode);
615  if (retVal != 0)
616  {
617  retVal = errCode;
618  goto exit;
619  }
620 
621 #ifndef MMW_ENABLE_NEGATIVE_FREQ_SLOPE
622  /* Check frequency slope */
623  if (profileCfg.freqSlopeConst < 0)
624  {
625  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOTSUPPORT__NEGATIVE_FREQ_SLOPE;
626  goto exit;
627  }
628 #endif
629 
630  outParams->numAdcSamples = profileCfg.numAdcSamples;
631  outParams->numRangeBins = mathUtils_pow2roundup(outParams->numAdcSamples);
632  outParams->numChirpsPerFrame = frameTotalChirps * numLoops;
633 
634  outParams->numDopplerChirps = outParams->numChirpsPerFrame/outParams->numTxAntennas;
635  outParams->numDopplerBins = mathUtils_pow2roundup(outParams->numDopplerChirps);
636  outParams->rangeStep = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_SPEED_OF_LIGHT_IN_METERS_PER_SEC * profileCfg.digOutSampleRate * 1e3 /
637  (2 * profileCfg.freqSlopeConst * ((rfFreqScaleFactor*1e3*900)/(1U << 26)) * 1e12 * outParams->numRangeBins);
638 
639  outParams->dopplerStep = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_SPEED_OF_LIGHT_IN_METERS_PER_SEC /
640  (2. * profileCfg.startFreqConst/(1U << 26)*rfFreqScaleFactor*1e9 *
641  (profileCfg.idleTimeConst+ profileCfg.rampEndTime)/1000.*10*1.e-6 *
642  outParams->numDopplerBins *
643  outParams->numTxAntennas);
644 #ifdef MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_DBG
645  System_printf("Ant setting virtualAzim: %d , virtual Elev :%d\n",
646  outParams->numVirtualAntAzim, outParams->numVirtualAntElev);
647 #endif
648 
649  }
650  }
651 exit:
652  return (retVal);
653 }

669 static int32_t MmwDemo_RFParser_parseADCBufCfg
670 (
671  MmwDemo_RFParserOutParams *outParams,
672  MmwDemo_ADCBufCfg *adcBufCfg
673 )
674 {
675  uint16_t numBytePerSample = 0;
676  uint32_t chirpThreshold;
677  uint32_t maxChirpThreshold;
678  uint32_t bytesPerChirp;
679  int32_t retVal = 0;
680 
681  /* Only support Complex */
682  if (adcBufCfg->adcFmt != 0)
683  {
684  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOTSUPPORT__NONCOMPLEX_ADC_FORMAT;
685  goto exit;
686  }
687 
688  /* Complex dataFormat has 4 bytes */
689  numBytePerSample = 4U;
690 
691  /* Calculate RX channel data size and make it align to 16 bytes */
692  outParams->adcBufChanDataSize = outParams->numAdcSamples * numBytePerSample;
693  outParams->adcBufChanDataSize = (outParams->adcBufChanDataSize + 15U) / 16U * 16U;
694 
695  /* Calculate max possible chirp threshold */
696  bytesPerChirp = outParams->adcBufChanDataSize * outParams->numRxAntennas;
697 
698  /* find maximum number of full chirps that can fit in the ADCBUF memory, while
699  also being able to divide numChirpsPerFrame, we do not want remainder processing */
700  maxChirpThreshold = MmwDemo_RFParserHwCfg.adcBufSize/ bytesPerChirp;
701  if (maxChirpThreshold >= outParams->numChirpsPerFrame)
702  {
703  maxChirpThreshold = outParams->numChirpsPerFrame;
704  if (maxChirpThreshold > SYS_COMMON_CQ_MAX_CHIRP_THRESHOLD)
705  {
706  /* If CQ monitor is enabled, then check max chirpthreshold */
707  maxChirpThreshold = SYS_COMMON_CQ_MAX_CHIRP_THRESHOLD;
708  }
709  }
710  else
711  {
712  /* Find largest divisor of numChirpsPerFrame no bigger than maxChirpThreshold */
713  while (outParams->numChirpsPerFrame % maxChirpThreshold)
714  {
715  maxChirpThreshold--;
716  }
717  }
718 
719  /* ADCBuf control function requires argument alignment at 4 bytes boundary */
720  chirpThreshold = adcBufCfg->chirpThreshold;
721 
722  /* if automatic, set to the calculated max */
723  if (chirpThreshold == 0)
724  {
725  chirpThreshold = maxChirpThreshold;
726  }
727  else
728  {
729  if (chirpThreshold > maxChirpThreshold)
730  {
731 #ifdef MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_DBG
732  System_printf("Desired chirpThreshold %d higher than max possible of %d, setting to max\n",
733  chirpThreshold, maxChirpThreshold);
734 #endif
735  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_EINVAL__CHIRP_THRESH_GREATER_THAN_MAX_ALLOWED;
736  goto exit;
737  }
738  else
739  {
740  /* check for divisibility of the user provided threshold */
741  if((outParams->numChirpsPerFrame % chirpThreshold) != 0)
742  {
743  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_ENOTSUPPORT__NON_DIVISIBILITY_OF_CHIRP_THRESH;
744  goto exit;
745  }
746  else
747  {
748  /* Chirp threshold has a valid configuration */
749  }
750  }
751  }
752 
753 #ifdef MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_DBG
754  System_printf(" chirpThreshold %d max = %d, \n",
755  chirpThreshold, maxChirpThreshold);
756 #endif
757 
758  /* Save chirpThreshold */
759  outParams->numChirpsPerChirpEvent = chirpThreshold;
760 
761 exit:
762  return (retVal);
763 }

789 int32_t MmwDemo_RFParser_parseConfig
790 (
791  MmwDemo_RFParserOutParams *outParams,
792  uint8_t subFrameIdx,
793  MMWave_OpenCfg *openCfg,
794  MMWave_CtrlCfg *ctrlCfg,
795  MmwDemo_ADCBufCfg *adcBufCfg,
796  float rfFreqScaleFactor
797 )
798 {
799  int32_t retVal;
800 
801  if(subFrameIdx < RL_MAX_SUBFRAMES)
802  {
803  /* Parse the profile and chirp configs and get the valid number of TX Antennas */
804  retVal = MmwDemo_RFParser_parseCtrlConfig(outParams, subFrameIdx,
805  openCfg, ctrlCfg, rfFreqScaleFactor);
806  if (retVal != 0)
807  {
808  goto exit;
809  }
810  retVal = MmwDemo_RFParser_parseADCBufCfg(outParams, adcBufCfg);
811  if (retVal != 0)
812  {
813  goto exit;
814  }
815  }
816  else
817  {
818  retVal = MMWDEMO_RFPARSER_EINVAL__NUM_SUBFRAMES;
819  }
820 
821 exit:
822  return retVal;
823 }
